  "prompt": "What is the most underrated problem in the life of a musician?",
  "response": "One of the most underrated problems in the life of a musician is the inconsistent income and financial instability. While some people might assume that musicians, especially successful ones, are financially secure, the reality is often very different. Many musicians face unpredictable and fluctuating income streams since gigs, royalties, and other revenue sources can be irregular. This financial uncertainty can create stress and challenges in managing everyday living expenses, health care, and investing in their careers.\n\nIn addition, musicians may struggle with balancing their passion for their art with the practical aspects of making a living, often taking on side jobs or gigs in unrelated fields to support themselves. This issue is exacerbated for those who are still working to gain recognition and establish themselves in the industry. The financial pressures can affect their mental health, creativity, and even their ability to continue pursuing their musical goals.",
